## v0.4
**Canonical Lineage and the Limits of Statistical Identity**

- Autocorrelation-based clone detection experiment (50 runs)
- Key finding: statistical metrics cannot separate clone from original
  - ORIG-FORK gap: -0.047 (not separable)
  - Attacker clearly separated: score 0.10 vs 0.52
- Two-layer identity model established:
  - Layer A: statistical anomaly detection (attacker detection)
  - Layer B: canonical lineage verification (clone discrimination)
- IEPP scope clarified: measurement layer only
- Open questions documented for application designers
- Future vision: genesis registry concept introduced

